# Login Page Design Guide

## Current Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/app/login/page.tsx` | Client component. Creates Supabase client, calls `signInWithOAuth({ provider: 'google' })`. Renders centered card with heading, subtitle, and `<GoogleSignInButton>`. |
| `src/components/login/GoogleSignInButton.tsx` | Client component. Styled button with Google "G" SVG icon and "Sign in with Google" text. Uses Tailwind classes. |
| `public/google-g.svg` | Google "G" logo asset. |
| `src/app/auth/callback/route.ts` | Server route handler. Exchanges OAuth code, redirects. NOT a visual page. |

## What You Have to Work With

- Tailwind CSS with slate/indigo color scheme.
- The page is a **client component** (needs `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth`).
- Only external auth provider is **Google**.

## Allowed Revisions

- `src/app/login/page.tsx` — layout and styling
- `src/components/login/GoogleSignInButton.tsx` — button styling
- `public/google-g.svg` — replace with updated asset

## Allowed New Files

- `src/components/login/` — additional login page components

## Constraints

- Do NOT modify `src/app/auth/callback/route.ts`.
- Do NOT modify files outside the login page scope.
- The `signInWithOAuth` call must remain functionally identical.
- Follow Google's branding guidelines for the sign-in button.
- Do NOT add new npm dependencies without explicit approval.
